[32m+[m[32m# Getting Started[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Developer Experience[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m-   Nodejs[m
[32m+[m[32m-   Express[m
[32m+[m[32m-   MongoDB[m
[32m+[m[32m-   Mongoose[m
[32m+[m[32m-   Postman[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Project setup for `Development`[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. We will use `yarn` as our package manager. So, install it by running the `command` bellow.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32mnpm i -g yarn[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Install `eslint` and `prettier` extension in your `vscode`.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Install `Postman` app on your computer.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m4. Clone project on your local machine by running `git clone https://github.com/Solutya/eCommerce-be`[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m5. Go to the project directory `eCommerce-be` and run `yarn` then `yarn prepare`.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m6. Create `.env` file in your root directory.Then copy the contents of `.env.example` to `.env`.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m7. Finally run `yarn dev` to start the dev server.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m8. API Documentation `https://documenter.getpostman.com/view/16600453/2s93RMUaew`[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**ENV**[m
[32m+[m[32m`PORT=8000`[m
[32m+[m[32m`NODE_ENV=development`[m
[32m+[m[32m`MONGO_URI=`[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m`JWT_SECRET=`[m
[32m+[m[32m`JWT_EXPIRES_IN=3d`[m
[32m+[m[32m`COOKIE_EXPIRE=5`[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m`SERVICE=gmail`[m
[32m+[m[32m`MAIL=`[m
[32m+[m[32m`PASSWORD=`[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m`EMAIL_SUBJECT="Do not share your OTP Sended from LOGO"`[m
